The paper discusses the use of Service-Oriented Architectures (SOAs) in modeling and simulation (M&S), which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MS (Modeling and Simulation) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of interoperability and composability in distributed M&S services, which could also place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of net-centric environments, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of formalism-based, model-driven, and ontology-driven frameworks, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.DL (Digital Libraries) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the crossover between the disciplines of M&S, service-orientation, and software/systems engineering, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
